## Command Execution Rules

### Never Chain Commands
```powershell
‚ùå Copy-Item "a.md" "b.md"; Copy-Item "c.md" "d.md"
‚úÖ Execute one command, wait, then next
```

### Limit Recursive Operations
```powershell
‚ùå Get-ChildItem -Recurse (without limits)
‚úÖ Get-ChildItem -Depth 1 or -Depth 2
```

### Single Operation Per Command
- One file copy at a time
- One directory creation at a time
- One validation check at a time

